title.12: Adventures on the Planet of the Apes (1975) #6
title.80: Adventures on the Planet of the Apes (1975) #5

description.0: The X-Men have always regarded Sentinels as the enemy. But after, Banshee, Jean Grey, and Wolverine are apprehended in space, they may have to place trust in a mutant-killing machine that claims to want them alive.
description.1: Johnny has taken time off from the Fantastic Four to focus on his relationship with Frankie Raye. But when a "golden gorilla" captures his sister, will Johnny save Sue...or his love life?
description.13: Peter has dinner with Aunt May and Dr. Octopus, who explains how he barely escaped with his life following a nuclear reactor explosion. As if things weren't strange enough, the spectral form of Hammerhead returns to haunt the dinner goers! What is the source of this strange apparition? And is Doc Ock as reformed a villain as he seems?
description.14: The remaining Squadron Supreme members set out to track down the Avengers and retrieve the Serpent Crown!
description.15: Captain America, Falcon, and General Fist have finally located the Madbomb assembly plant. But the Madbomb has been moved! Can the trio find it before it goes off?
description.16: The streets of Los Angeles are rocked by Rampage! The Champions have an impressive confrontation with Stuart Clarke...but can they withstand the villain's weaponized suit? Plus, Black Widow becomes official team leader!
description.17: Fawn alerts Mar-Vell of Rick Jones' condition, and the Captain rushes to the rescue!
description.18: The Jester nearly bungles Foggy Nelson’s chances at becoming District Attorney!
description.26: After viewing a late night Kung-Fu movie with Beverly, Howard finds himself in an ugly brawl. The effects of the blood shed hit Howard hard and he decides that he must learn the arts of Kung-Fu!
description.29: Doc Samson and S.H.I.E.L.D. embark for Florida to retrieve the Hulk. Betty is tormented with guilt over her passion with Doc Samson.
description.30: When Blizzard targets Stark Industries in search of the climatron, Iron Man must rocket into action to save the lives of his employees as well as everybody on the planet! For if Blizzard gets his hands on the climatron, we're sure to see the next Ice Age!
description.31: Just as James-Michael is getting settled into his new safe-haven with Amber and Ruth, an encounter with the Hulk causes the awakening of the Unknown - putting James-Michael in serious peril!
description.32: Thor and Firelord fall under the spell of the Gypsy!
description.33: When Wong ends up bitten by a vampire, Dr. Strange's investigation may lead him straigh to the door of the greatest vampire of all - Dracula! Plus, Blade and Deacon Frost!
description.34: The Thing is back! Reed designs a special exo-suit that simulates the Thing's powers when Ben wears it. Meanwhile, it is discovered that an evil outsider is responsible for Power Man's outbursts. But who?
description.37: It's not a comic book wedding till a super-villain arrives! Mirage, a petty thief turned criminal mastermind, crashes the wedding of Betty Brant and Ned Leeds. Will Spidey be able to save this special day? Or will Peter Parker's identity once again be threatened in front of friends and family? Plus, Aunt May receives a surprise visit from none other than Dr. Octopus!
description.38: The Avengers and the Squadron Supreme have been transported to the Squadron's Earth following a battle at the Brant Corporation.
description.39: Captain America takes on a whole swath of murderous warriors underground!
description.43: PANTHER'S RAGE: PART 16: The Panther intervenes at another Ku Klux Klan rally. What happens next is a historic showdown you can't miss!
description.57: A big tent battle between Bullseye and Daredevil! DD's locked in combat in the center ring of a circus...and hundreds of spectators are getting the smackdown of a show! But the Man Without Fear isn't without a few tricks of his own.
description.58: Guest-starring Daimon Hellstrom! Katy's health takes a turn for the worse when she falls under demonic possession! The Son of Satan answers the call to save her.
description.59: The Hulk is aboard The Collector's ship where the villain has mutants and humanoids on display in his own personal museum. Will Hulk free the "exhibits"...or be tempted by The Collector's cure for Banner's condition?
description.60: Happy Hogan has become a living bomb! If Iron Man doesn't stop him thousands of lives will be lost! But if he does, the life of his dearest friend will be lost instead! Plus: Witness the dramatic new change in Iron Man's armor!
description.61: Bucky's in charge of a brand new superteam called the Liberty Legion. Their first mission: take down the Invaders!
description.62: Balder starts to suspect Odin has lost his mind while Thor and Jane look to aid Firelord with a rebellion in Costa Verde.
description.63: A sleepy winter night turns into a race for survival, as a news reporter crosses paths with Dracula!
description.64: Pip takes center-stage in this 'Trollish Tale'! Marvel's most dastardly troll runs into trouble at a cabaret, when performer Heater Delight catches his eye. But before love can bloom, Pip must take on Pro-Boscis, Heater's unrelenting, (and entirely cruel), owner!
description.65: It's a feel-good Christmas issue! On the eve before the holiday, the X-Men split paths to celebrate Yuletide in their own ways. Shopping with Storm! Date night for Jean Grey and Cyclops! Wolverine sulking alone! But how will this night of festivities end for the mutants? Knowing the X-Men, the merry times just can't keep rolling.
description.66: Ben finds himself at the bottom of a bottle since losing his powers. Meanwhile, Power Man has snapped and begins attacking his FF teammates! With a vacancy in the team yet again, Ben's replacement has to be the next best "Thing"!
description.74: When a high-powered computer engineer is found dead, Spider-Man must investigate all possible motives. What is the Worldwide Habitual Offender Computer? And what happens when such a powerful program develops sentience?
description.75: The Assassin has poisoned Captain America with a dose of lethal radiation. Thor, as Dr. Donald Blake, will go to great lengths to save his teammate from death. To cover the absence of Thor, Iron Man creates a Life Model Decoy that will fight the Assassin alongside the rest of the team.
description.76: Captain America and the Falcon find themselves in a middle of the Kill-Derby! It's a battle to the death for these gladiators! The rules: Anything goes! Don't miss out on the Kill-Derby games!
description.77: Angel decides to pay his vast inheritance forward, establishing a 'super hero service' for the Champions. But while Warren Worthington gains more wealth, industrialist Stuart Clarke is all the poorer. Near bankruptcy, a desperate Clarke dons an armored suit...and begins his career as a bank robber!
description.82: Featuring Daimon Hellstrom, the Son of Satan, and the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing! The unlikely pair come across a strange disturbance in Arizona, where they are confronted by the undead spirits of outlaws of the Old West!
description.85: If Captain America is for the people, what happens when the people turn against him? Can Cap and Falc keep the peace? Or will they fail, costing them everything they hold dear? The savage world of 1984 is here!
description.86: The Supreme Intelligence brings Captain Marvel and Drax the Destroyer out to a desolate moon to confront one another!
description.88: Bullseye's first appearance! In the debut of Marvel's most manic marksman, Daredevil learns that his adversary's quite the showman- and DD's been lured into a very public battle!
description.89: The Collector is on the hunt, and he's looking to add the Hulk to his collection! And he's got a green giant of his own the battle the Hulk for dominance - the mysterious Man-Thing!
description.90: He's back! The most furious of all foes-the fearsome Freak! A city trembles in fear, and not even Iron Man can save it-not on the night of the walking bomb!
description.91: Introducing the story of James-Michael Starling, a shy but intelligent boy with a dark secret! Every night, he is tortured by nightmares of battling an android race in the future! But little does he know that his life is about to change forever...
description.92: The Lord of Vampires teams up with the ultimate vampire hunter! Wait, what!? Blade and Dracula fight side-by-side to end the menace of Doctur Sun!
description.93: "Be careful what you wish for, because you just might get it!" The FF replaces Ben Grimm with Power Man, as the Thing is now powerless. The Wrecker wreaks havoc, and Ben decides to prove himself to his old team. But does he have what it takes without his powers?
description.95: Frustrated over Dr. Bolton's death, Spider-Man takes out his aggression on common criminals. But what happens when Spider-Man goes too far with a street thug? Plus, the return of Sandman! And this time, the villain finds himself in a criminal enclave equipped with cryogenic technology!
description.96: The mysterious masked villain, Assassin, swears the Avengers will be dead within the year. What are his motives? And how will the team defend themselves against their most vengeful enemy yet?
description.97: The team becomes acquainted with the weird science of Dr. Edward Lansing. The ambitious Lansing is determined to create a Super Solider Serum...and the Champions prove perfect guinea pigs!

2.text: On the first night in the dorms of his new job, Daimon is visited by the oracle Proffit who foresees an ill fate for Daimon and his new coworker, Saripha Thames.

3.text: Red Wolf guest-stars! Tigra gets an assist while taking on the aptly named Rat Pack!

4.text: Swordquest starts here! Meet Shimuru Kurasu, a fearsome samurai with a unique destiny!

5.text: After all these years, Maximus has won...and no one can save the Inhumans now!

6.text: Martial arts madness in the mighty Marvel manner - featuring appearances from M'Nai and Cho Lin!

7.text: Vulcan and his men break into Stark Industries to steal a potential deadly weapon!

10.text: A bigoted arsonist named Wildfire targets an African American family. Thankfully, Luke Cage is on the case to douse his flames!

11.text: The Guardians of the Galaxy find themselves on the Planet of the Absurd and are branded as hostile invaders!

12.text: Taylor and Nova venture out alone into the forbidden zone and the greatest secret of the Planet of The Apes is revealed!

17.text: Fawn alerts Mar-Vell of Rick Jones' condition, and the Captain rushes to the rescue!

18.text: The Jester nearly bungles Foggy Nelson’s chances at becoming District Attorney!

20.text: The Liberty Legion show up at the Invaders darkest hour as they are forced to fight Captain America and his team...who are being controlled by the maniacal Red Skull!

21.text: Doc Strange, transformed into that which he fears most- a vampire!

22.text: Jack Norriss, reunited with his brain at last! Doctor Strange calls in a Russian neurosurgeon for the most complicated procedure of his career. Chondu is trapped in a transient state…and it’s taken quite a toll on his body!

24.text: Morbius the Living Vampire and the Thing band together as one deadly duo.

25.text: While trying to head back to his own time, Spider-Man is transported to the year 2019… and finds himself in the middle of Killraven's rebellion against Earth's Martian Masters!

28.text: The first appearance of Deathraven, brother of Killraven! Will brotherly love foster in the war-torn waste fields of a fallen Earth? Plus, a Martian nursery!

36.text: Deathlok discovers a way to switch his mind and body with Simon Ryker. Driven to madness in Deathlok’s body, Ryker is no longer a threat. With Ryker destroyed, Deathlok accepts a new mission from the C.I.A. But will Luther Manning lose his humanity as he continues to be a weapon-for-hire?

40.text: Iron Fist does battle for the Bird of Fire!

41.text: Piranha Jones takes Power Man as his prisoner!

42.text: Shang-Chi, the son of Fu Manchu, battles his father's league of deadly assassins in "The Murder Agency!"

43.text: The Panther intervenes at a Ku Klux Klan rally. What happens next is a historic showdown you can’t miss!

44.text: A new arc for Jack Russell! Will Werewolf by Night help a desperate father seeking custody of his baby daughter?

46.text: Skull becomes de-facto leader of the crew, despite mistrust all around. The battle in Camelot rages on, as Black Knight and Skull take on Morgan Le Fay. But why are the scientists fighting on Morgan’s side? Skull and his comrades make a hasty escape from the Tower of Time, but not before discovering a shocking secret about Black Knight and the rest of Arthur's court!

48.text: Namor in custody of the Fantastic Four! After Doom pulls the wool over his eyes, (and the air from his lungs), Namor recounts his failed alliance to the FF. Namor plots his revenge against the Latverian overlord, but his failing health puts him in grave danger! Will Doom relinquish the cure for Namor?

49.text: Doctor Strange is the only survivor after the destruction of the planet! Can he convince Eternity to restore Earth back to it's former glory?

50.text: Hulk fears the worst when his beloved pet Bambi goes missing. Nebulon explains his extraterrestrial plans to “Nighthawk”.  What exactly is a Celestial Mind Control Seminar?

51.text: London’s on the verge of a radioactive melt-down, as Iron Fist takes on Radion! Danny Rand must call on his K'un-Lun teachings to heal himself, and find the spiritual guidance necessary to take down his worst foe yet. Who was Henri Sorel before he was a being of pure energy? Your answers revealed in this issue!

52.text: Moondragon is pulled into the year 1692 by Scarlet Witch’s magic, and provides aid to Scarlet Witch, Spider-Man, the Vision and Doctor Doom as they battle the Dark Rider!

53.text: An untold tale of Prince Namor, the Sub-Mariner, as he fights alone against the mystery and terror of…the SYMBIONIC MAN!

56.text: The Possessor has his plan to take over Hell from under Satan's feet, but not if the Son of Satan can help it!

67.text: Iron Fist continues to duke it out with Dhasha Khan! Meanwhile, Hector Ayala struggles in his White Tiger persona.

68.text: His masters sent him to capture the Inhumans...and Shatterstar always delivers!

69.text: Luke looks down the barrel of Cockroach Hamilton’s custom shotgun!

70.text: It's Shang-Chi versus the Cat in the Master of Kung Fu’s most equally-skilled match yet!

71.text: Black Goliath battles the Atom Smasher and Warhawk!

78.text: The Guardians of the Galaxy encounter Karanada, entities capable of consuming entire galaxies!

79.text: It’s catlike reflexes vs. brute animal rage as Tigra takes on Kraven the Hunter!

80.text: Taylor, Nova, Zira and Cornelius are fugitives as they flee to the forbidden zone. What they'll find in the wastelands beyond Ape City will shock them all, human and ape alike!

82.text: Featuring Daimon Hellstrom, the Son of Satan, and the ever-lovin' blue-eyed Thing! The unlikely pair come across a strange disturbance in Arizona, where they are confronted by the undead spirits of outlaws of the Old West!

83.text: Enter: the Red Skull!  The scourge of World War II is sent to destroy Captain America and the Invaders...and he just might succeed!

84.text: The Defenders brace themselves for full mind/body swaps courtesy of the Headmen. But the team won’t go down without a fight! Chondu’s trapped in the body of Bambi. All that and an alien abduction!

86.text: The Supreme Intelligence brings Captain Marvel and Drax the Destroyer out to a desolate moon to confront one another!

87.text: With the world in ruins, Thor and his companions - along with the Tomorrow Man and his Servitor - make a last-ditch effort to save the fate of not only Zarrko's world, but also that of all worlds. But will even a trip to the end of time be enough to stop the awesome chain of events that threatens every living being? The Thunder God is faced with challenges unlike any seen before in this, the ultimate chapter of the Saga of the Time Twisters!

98.text: The scientists and Skull take a beating in the Tower of Time, an alien construct filled with dimensional wormholes. But when the three scientists seemingly perish at the hands of Slitherouge, guardian of the Tower, it’s up to Skull to save the mission! Skull the Slayer thrown into the Arthurian court of Camelot! Guest-starring Merlin and the Black Knight.

99.text: After failing to detach an explosive on his wrist, Deathlok loses his bionic arm and much of his body. Mike Travers, anti-hero, manages to retrieve Deathlok’s body from the blast and takes him to the C.I.A for tinkering. There, Deathlok is re-programmed with one mission operative; take down Simon Ryker once and for all. Ryker re-invents himself as the half-cyborg, Savior Machine.
